<BR/>The elevator boy tips his cap nervously, slams the gate shut, and beats a quick retreat down to safer floors.
<BR/>You approach Croghan's imposing mahogany desk with care. The man himself sits behind it, tall as a linebacker but whisper-thin, a face all angles and edges balanced above a charcoal-grey bow tie, immaculately tied. He smokes a Diego cigar with one wiry hand while riffling through the box office reports with the other.
<BR/>He hasn't looked up. How to get his attention?
<BR/><B>CHOICES:</B>
- Wait for him to notice me.
- Cough politely.
- Announce myself.
</pre></td><td class="gutter"></td>
